{
 "schema_version": "1.0",
 "id": "form47",
 "kind": "curve",
 "meta": {
  "title": "Risk of recurrent seizures after two unprovoked seizures",
  "doi": "10.1056/NEJM199802123380704",
  "authors": "Hauser WA, Rich SS, Lee JR, et al.",
  "journal": "New England Journal of Medicine",
  "year": 1998,
  "outcome": "Cumulative recurrence risk and COSY, by number of prior seizures or by aetiology (Hauser et al., 1998)",
  "cff_info": "<h3>Background</h3>\n<p>This tool provides a personalized risk assessment for seizure recurrence and the chance of an occurrence of a seizure in the next year (COSY). It is based on a register-based cohort study that analyzed the risk of seizure recurrence after one or more unprovoked seizures.</p>\n<h3>Study basis</h3>\n<p>The calculator is derived from a long-term cohort study of 204 patients investigating the probability of seizure recurrence in patients with a history of unprovoked seizures &mdash; including individuals with remote symptomatic epilepsy and idiopathic epilepsy &mdash; quantifying seizure risk over time.</p>\n<h3>Variables used</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>History of seizures</strong> &mdash; the risk of recurrence increases with each additional seizure; the calculator adjusts for whether the patient has had one, two, or more unprovoked seizures.</li>\n<li><strong>Seizure type</strong> &mdash; <em>remote symptomatic epilepsy</em>: linked to prior neurological conditions such as traumatic brain injury, stroke, or infection; <em>idiopathic epilepsy</em>: seizures occur without a known structural or metabolic cause, often with a genetic predisposition.</li>\n<li><strong>Time since last seizure</strong> &mdash; calculations update dynamically at the selected time point, reflecting changes in long-term recurrence probability.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Outputs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cumulative seizure-recurrence risk</strong> &mdash; plotted over time, so you can see how seizure history and epilepsy type influence recurrence probability.</li>\n<li><strong>Chance of an occurrence of a seizure in the next year (COSY)</strong> &mdash; informs whether an individual may be fit to drive, based on their specific seizure-recurrence risk.</li>\n</ul>"
 },
 "thresholds": {
  "group1": 20.0,
  "group2": 2.0
 },
